Kanpur:Â                             A 30-year-old woman died after being allegedly raped and burnt alive by her neighbour, Kanpur police said today.
The victim was alone at home in Panki district yesterday when the accused Brajkishore raped her and then set her on fire, she had told her neighbours, they said. The victim's husband Zulfiqar, who was working in the fields, rushed home after the neighours informed him about the incident. He found the victim partially burnt and immediately rushed her to the hospital, where she died last night, police said.
Her family alleged that police was initially reluctant to lodge a First Information Report, but when they complained to city Senior Superintendent of Police, Shailabh Mathur, a case of rape and murder was registered against Brajkishore.
A hunt has been launched to nab the accused.(This story has not been edited by NDTV staff and is auto-generated from a syndicated feed.)

